I've always been a fan of this restaurant, but the food I had last night blew me away! I ordered the Lacinato Kale and Beet because I saw it was a top menu item, and I have to say, it definitely deserves that top spot! The herbed goat cheese was creamy and delicious and I especially loved the addition of the roasted beets. Definitely a must order if you're in the area!

The Dubliner is definitely my go-to place whenever I have friends coming to visit the city! They're always impressed by the quality of the food, but I have to say, it was probably the best its ever been when we went this past Sunday! I always recommend they try the Craic Burger (my personal favorite) when we're there. I could eat just the fries for a whole meal because they're so good, but all of the food is delicious! Highly recommend this place to anyone looking for a good dinner and great service!

This place offers consistently good food, including somewhat authentic Irish fares - shepherd's pie, Irish stew and British choices like bangers and mash and fish and chips. I've had their burgers before and during lunch rush they are good, however, if you come after 2, you are out of luck- you'll be served with leftovers from lunch. Cant say anything about dinner though since I've never been here after 4. Also decent selection of beer and prices are not eye gauging. The service is consistently slow whether its lunch/ dinner rush or in between slow-down, not for when you are in a rush to get back to work but ok for when you just want to sit and chill.

I went there twice, never again. Both times had a horrible experience. Awful service, chairs and booths stink and music sux! The waitress was rude and was rolling her eyes on us and was giving us an attitude. She did not know anything about the food either. We were still eating and drinking when she brought the check without asking if we want to split it, then barked at us "tip is not included in the price!" And walked away.  The time before that I took my co-workers for lunch. They messed up most of our orders. I clearly said that I have a dairy allergy and told them not to put cheese on my portabella mushroom sandwich. They brought a wrong sandwich twice! I left them a decent tip anyways. A few days later I checked my bank account and they added additional $30 on top of what I already gave them! I would argue the bill but I don't have the receipt anymore. Don't go there. There are a lot of other bars in the area that are much better.
